Problem:
class WeatherSimulator {
    private int temperature;
    private boolean isRaining;

    public WeatherSimulator(int temp) {
        temperature = temp;
        isRaining = false;
    }

    public void adjustWeather(boolean rainy, int tempChange) {
        isRaining = rainy;
        temperature += tempChange;
        if (isRaining && temperature < 0) {
            System.out.println('Snowing because it is cold and raining.');
        } else if (isRaining) {
            System.out.println('Just raining.');
        } else if (temperature >= 35) {
            System.out.println('Hot and sunny.');
        }
    }
}",

If the temperature is initially set to 5 degrees Celsius and no intervention is made, will the system naturally lead to snow?
